parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description:
The client token that is used to ensure the idempotence of the request.

You can use the client to generate the value, but you must make sure that it is unique among all requests. The token can contain only ASCII characters.

parameters.name: DryRun
parameters.description:
Specifies whether to perform a dry run. Valid values:

*   **true**: performs a dry run. The system checks the required parameters, request syntax, and limits. If the request fails the dry run, an error message is returned. If the request passes the dry run, the `DryRunOperation` error code is returned.
*   **false** (default): performs a dry run and sends the request.

parameters.name: GroupIpAddress
parameters.description: The IP address of the multicast group to which the multicast source belongs.

parameters.name: NetworkInterfaceIds
parameters.description: The IDs of the multicast sources that you want to delete.

parameters.name: TransitRouterMulticastDomainId
parameters.description: The ID of the multicast domain to which the multicast source belongs.
